### Problem

The lsp client doesn't send `<TAB>` character correctly in the `textDocument/didChange` event when using `softtabstop = -1`. I ran into this because [vim-sleuth](https://github.com/tpope/vim-sleuth) sets `softtabstop` to `-1` by default.

**edit:** This also happens if you set `tabstop` and `shiftwidth` to different values.

### Steps to reproduce using "nvim -u minimal_init.lua"

``` lua
vim.o.shiftwidth = 0
vim.o.softtabstop = -1

vim.cmd.packadd("nvim-lspconfig")

vim.lsp.set_log_level("debug")

require('lspconfig').gopls.setup({})
```

I've created a repo with a minimal `init.lua` and steps to reproduce. https://github.com/icholy/nvim-lsp-bug

![tty](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/943597/9289ead4-0159-4fab-9c9b-ea1f4fd98f3e)

**Note**: I've been able to reproduce this with several lsp servers.

### Expected behavior

Send a single tab character in `textDocument/didChange`

``` lua
{
    jsonrpc = "2.0",
    method = "textDocument/didChange",
    params = {
        contentChanges = {
            {
                range = {["end"] = {character = 0, line = 0}, start = {character = 0, line = 0}},
                rangeLength = 0,
                text = "\t"
            }
        },
        textDocument = {uri = "file:///home/icholy/src/github.com/icholy/nvim-lsp-bug/main.go", version = 4}
    }
}
```

